SIMPLE: costa
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Costa
<hw>Cos"ta</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocr⟧s"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.,
rib. See <er>Coast</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A
rib of an animal or a human being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A rib or vein of a leaf,
especially the midrib.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The anterior rib in
the wing of an insect.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the riblike
longitudinal ridges on the exterior of many corals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Costage</ent>⟦br⟧
